			<article class="uk-article">

				<h1 class="uk-article-title">
					<a n:href="this">ipub:Gravatar!</a>
				</h1>

				<p class="uk-article-meta">Written by Doe John on 12 April 2013. Posted in <a href="#">Extensions demo</a></p>

				<p>
					<a href="#"><img width="900" height="300" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," alt=""></a>
				</p>

				<h2>N:macro</h2>

				<p>You can use n:macro <strong>n:gravatar</strong> and this macro will automatically create SRC or HREF parameter of attribute, it depends on the attribute type.</p>

				<pre><code>&lt;img n:gravatar="'john@doe.com', 100" /&gt;</code></pre>

				<pre><code>&lt;div class="uk-panel uk-panel-box uk-text-center"&gt;
	&lt;img n:gravatar="'john@doe.com', 120" class="uk-border-circle" width="120" height="120" alt="Avatar" /&gt;

	&lt;h3&gt;John Doe&lt;/h3&gt;

	&lt;p&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisici elit, sed eiusmod tempor incidunt ut.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>

				<h2>Latte macro</h2>

				<p>If you need to create just only link for gravatar image, you can use classic latte macro <strong>{l}gravatar{r}</strong></p>

				<pre><code>{l}gravatar 'john@doe.com', 120{r}</code></pre>

				<pre><code>&lt;div class="uk-panel uk-panel-box uk-text-center"&gt;
	&lt;img src="{l}gravatar 'john@doe.com', 120{r}" class="uk-border-circle" width="120" height="120" alt="Avatar" /&gt;

	&lt;h3&gt;John Doe&lt;/h3&gt;

	&lt;p&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisici elit, sed eiusmod tempor incidunt ut.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>

			</article>
